%description:
TCP AccECN (Workstream G) G1.1: tcpEcnMode supersedes the deprecated
ecnWillingness parameter. This commit is pure param plumbing -- with
tcpEcnMode="rfc3168" (and ecnWillingness left at its default, unset), the
wire trace must be byte-for-byte identical to today's ecnWillingness=true
behavior, since state->ecnWillingness is kept in sync (ecnMode>=2) so every
existing classic-ECN call site is unmodified.

This test pins the tcpEcnMode="rfc3168" trace directly (a simple ECN-willing
active-open connection: SYN carries ECE+CWR, the SYN-ACK echoes ECE only,
per RFC 3168 SS6.1). Byte-for-byte equivalence with the legacy
ecnWillingness=true path was verified empirically during development (same
scenario, same assertions, with ecnWillingness=true and tcpEcnMode="off"
instead) -- not repeated as a permanent second file since it exercises no
code this test doesn't already cover.

Falsification: setting both ecnWillingness=true AND tcpEcnMode to a
non-"off" value must throw "Tcp: set either the deprecated ecnWillingness or
tcpEcnMode, not both" -- verified empirically during development (temporarily
set both in this test's ini, confirmed the cRuntimeError fired with that
exact message), not pinned as a permanent assertion here since this test's
primary job is the plumbing-preserves-behavior claim, not exercising the
guard itself.

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false
*.tcptester.script=""

*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=-1s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=0B
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s
*.cli_app.sendScript=""

*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s
*.srv_app.sendScript=""

*.*_tcp.sackSupport = false
*.*_tcp.windowScalingSupport = false
*.*_tcp.timestampSupport = false
*.*_tcp.mss = 1000
*.*_tcp.tcpAlgorithmClass = "TcpReno"

*.*_tcp.tcpEcnMode = "rfc3168"

include ../../lib/tcp-legacy.ini

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: postrun.pl
open FILE, '<test.out';
while($sor = <FILE>)
{
    if ($sor =~ /^\[testing\]: (.*)$/)
    {
        print "$1\n";
    }
}
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command:  perl ./postrun.pl
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# SYN: ECE+CWR both set (RFC 3168 SS6.1's ECN-setup SYN, requesting ECN).
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.001 A001] A.1000 > B.2000: S E W 0:0(0) win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# SYN-ACK: ECE only (no CWR) -- the listener accepting the ECN-setup SYN.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.003 B001] A.1000 < B.2000: A S E 500:500(0) ack 1 win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
